# GitHub issues

- Write **all issues in English** (title and body). Do not create Portuguese issues.
- Prefer Conventional Commit-style titles when helpful (`ci: …`, `docs: …`, `feat: …`).

When you implement a GitHub issue:

1. Read the full issue body (scope, acceptance criteria, notes) before and during the work.
2. After implementation finishes, **edit the issue**:
   - Check completed checklist items (`- [x]`).
   - Leave incomplete items unchecked and note what remains.
   - Update acceptance criteria the same way.
3. Comment with a short English summary of what shipped and any follow-ups.
4. Close only when acceptance criteria are met; otherwise leave open/reopen with pending items visible.

See `CONTRIBUTING.md` and `AGENTS.md`.
